      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The perception of beauty can vary significantly across cultures and regions. In many Western cultures, symmetrical features and a clear complexion are traditionally seen as attractive. However, features such as wider eyes, full lips, and smooth skin have global appeal. While there is some level of universal attraction towards certain facial traits, it's essential to consider regional preferences and cultural variations in your global skincare line. Audience-specific tailoring of marketing strategies based on localized insights would be valuable.",
