      "content": "Generally, for people of East Asian descent, less makeup is often appreciated, with natural, oval-shaped faces being more desirable. High cheekbones, slightly smaller noses, and gentle, upward curves at the corners of the eyes are considered attractive. For someone of African descent, features that convey dynamism and emotionality are often sought after, with full lips and well-defined cheekbones being significant. However, note that these are broad trends and that individual preferences are diverse. For a global skincare brand, it is crucial to avoid reinforcing limiting stereotypes and to focus on creating an inclusive brand that respects and celebrates diversity within and across ethnicities. Aligning marketing efforts with these insights could help resonate with the target demographics more effectively.",
